## ğŸ¯ BEM Methodology

### Naming Convention
```
.block {}
.block__element {}
.block--modifier {}
.block__element--modifier {}
```

### Examples
```css
/* Block */
.card {}

/* Element */
.card__title {}
.card__image {}
.card__content {}
.card__button {}

/* Modifier */
.card--featured {}
.card--horizontal {}
.card__button--primary {}
.card__button--secondary {}
```

### BEM Rules
1. Block names: lowercase, hyphen-separated (e.g., `service-card`)
2. Element separator: double underscore `__`
3. Modifier separator: double hyphen `--`
4. Never nest more than 2 levels (block__element is max, not block__element__subelement)
5. Modifiers should be descriptive (e.g., `--large`, `--primary`, `--active`)

